OL,7,FThe route was treacherous due to its
OL,8,Fproximity to Nazi-occupied Norway and
OL,9,Fbecause of the conditions, with ice
OL,10,Fwhich formed around the ship's mast
OL,11,Fhaving to be removed by sailors using
OL,12,Fa blowtorch as it caused so much
OL,13,Finstability.
OL,15,FHMS Trinidad, which was sailing to
OL,16,Fundergo maintenance, was attacked by
OL,17,FNazi warplanes after leaving Murmansk,
OL,18,FRussia, with 750 evacuated and 50
OL,19,Fkilled before it was scuttled by
OL,20,FBritish destroyers prior to dawn on
OL,21,FMay 16, 1942.
